My team is trying to implement advantage kit and we are encountering some errors.

Here is what we did: installed the advantage kit vendordeps, updated the build.gradle file, copied below, we updated the robot.java file to start the logging, also copied below, and added a constants file to change the  simulation mode.

Right now we can run simulation and recieve logging in the advantage kit. Then that log gets saved in the logs folder, then the issue comes when we attempt to run the replay, here is my error: Error at org.littletonrobotics.junction.wpilog.WPILOGReader.start(WPILOGReader.java:61): [AdvantageKit] The replay log was not produced by AdvantageKit. at org.littletonrobotics.junction.wpilog.WPILOGReader.start(WPILOGReader.java:61) at org.littletonrobotics.junction.Logger.start(Logger.java:183) at frc.robot.Robot.(Robot.java:99) at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:370) at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.lambda$startRobot$1(RobotBase.java:490) at java.base/java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:840)

then the simulation opens a new log on advantage scope that has nothing on it except for a data called timestamp.

I put the entire files on there in case you guys see something related that we didn’t catch

